HEADWORD: Revivor
<hw>Re*viv"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>Revival of a suit which is abated by the death or marriage of any
of the parties, -- done by a bill of <xex>revivor</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

